        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "As defined in the {{Zend_Application_Bootstrap_BootstrapAbstract}} class, any component is initialized using the configuration file {{resources}} key. This is fine, as most resources have required initialization options. However, when a resource don't have such options, in order to initialize is needed to cheat the bootstrap object by using a dumb options like {{resources.customResource = \"\"}}.\r\n\r\nMy suggestion is that if the bootstrap object received a {{pluginPaths}} option then it could additionally look inside a resource plugins repositories ({{application\/resources}} for instance) and automatically initializes any resource within it - by reading the directories entries.\r\n\r\nThats all"
        },
